Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.08,0:00:48.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iread your letter.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.58,0:00:51.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're really going, then?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.95,0:01:03.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That day... I figured that William\Nboy must have met up with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.46,0:01:06.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.10,0:01:13.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Perhaps I said too much and scared him off.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.14,0:01:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It might sound conceited of me to say so,\Nbut I don't think that's the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.48,0:01:34.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... sometimes, trying to be considerate\Ncan make a person hesitate...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.52,0:01:39.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, he should at least see you off!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.70,0:01:48.64,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,Episode 12\NLilies of the Valley
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.05,0:02:03.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. So you're going to retire\Nfrom being a governess?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:04.02,0:02:06.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes. I'm getting on in years.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.12,0:02:09.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I need to take things easier.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:11.09,0:02:12.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who's this girl?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.53,0:02:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, she's a girl who was living on the streets.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:16.00,0:02:20.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She here came looking for work,\Nso I use her for simple jobs.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.54,0:02:25.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She looks intelligent.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.81,0:02:30.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Which reminds me, I've been wanting a maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.38,0:02:36.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come now Kelly, you can't be serious.\NShe's not the type you can train to be a maid.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.79,0:02:44.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's perfect. I've always wondered how much\Ncan be accomplished through education.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.89,0:02:45.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:47.40,0:02:49.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll teach you everything from scratch.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.20,0:02:51.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Will you come with me?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.70,0:02:54.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.04,0:02:56.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's it, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.50,0:02:57.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine with you, I trust?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.01,0:02:59.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Honestly...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.51,0:03:01.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame me if you regret it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.62,0:04:49.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.79,0:04:51.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...ma'am.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.81,0:05:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red sky at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.27,0:05:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red sky at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.04,0:05:17.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shepherd's delight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.21,0:05:20.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shepherd's delight.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.62,0:05:22.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red sky in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.92,0:05:25.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Red sky in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.25,0:05:26.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shepherd's warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.09,0:05:28.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shepherd's warning.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.19,0:05:31.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Vivi?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.03,0:05:34.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not my fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.26,0:05:37.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It takes a lot for father to raise\Nhis hand against someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:38.07,0:05:42.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it was bound to happen sooner or later.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.67,0:05:47.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry, Colin.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.84,0:05:52.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like they say, if it rains\Nbefore 7, it'll be fine by 1 1.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.88,0:05:55.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Brother Will will be fine soon, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.22,0:05:57.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So there's no need to fret.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.79,0:06:06.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is William ready to go?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.86,0:06:10.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, sir... he appears to be in his room, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.91,0:06:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.34,0:06:22.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,William, open the door!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.61,0:06:25.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,William!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.00,0:06:49.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, you've finally decided to come out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:50.61,0:06:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only because I wanted to get away.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.88,0:07:03.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When she really needed someone\Nby her side... I couldn't be there for her.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.92,0:07:09.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did l... ever really know her?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.43,0:07:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was only thinking of myself. I didn't\Nconsider what would make Emma happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.53,0:07:22.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well... I wanted to consider her feelings.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.37,0:07:29.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But Emma was suffering so badly.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.41,0:07:36.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if I decided to marry Emma,\Nshe would have to take on the Jones name.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.72,0:07:41.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She'd be bound by the strict traditions of\Npolite society, exposed to the curiosity of others...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.06,0:07:50.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sacrificing so much, would Emma\Never really be happy marrying me, I wonder?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.10,0:07:55.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Am I even a worthy partner for Emma?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.31,0:08:01.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I think of it... I become\Ntoo afraid to face her.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:03.38,0:08:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go ahead and call me spineless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.31,0:08:08.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are undoubtedly spineless.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.35,0:08:11.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Also miserable, and pathetic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.19,0:08:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're not prepared to lose Emma,\Nyet you keep acting all melodramatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.43,0:08:20.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.43,0:08:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're overdoing it a bit, aren't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.03,0:08:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You asked me to say it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.94,0:08:30.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You love Emma...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.21,0:08:32.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and Emma loves you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.67,0:08:37.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What else do you want?\NWhy are you so confused?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.61,0:08:40.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't understand you at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.89,0:08:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,More importantly, if you don't hurry and\Nstop Emma, you'll never see her again.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.26,0:08:55.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.33,0:08:59.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma said she was going\Nback to her childhood home.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.73,0:09:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.54,0:09:03.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why didn't you say that sooner?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.11,0:09:09.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Because I didn't really want to tell you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.48,0:09:48.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please summon the coachman.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.85,0:09:49.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.12,0:09:51.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.72,0:09:54.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong? Quickly now, hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.43,0:10:02.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eleanor...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.63,0:10:09.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was told to ask you out for a ride,\Nbut there must have been some mistake...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.97,0:10:13.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.74,0:10:15.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.05,0:10:24.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eleanor, you have to know. I...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.55,0:10:26.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll wait for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.09,0:10:26.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What...?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.76,0:10:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't have to be today, or tomorrow.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.90,0:10:37.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I really don't mind...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.83,0:10:41.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So please, invite me out again...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.84,0:10:44.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...because, I'm waiting for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.82,0:11:01.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please prepare the carriage.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.22,0:11:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir. Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.22,0:11:02.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Marylebone. Hurry up!\NYes, sir. Where to?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.62,0:11:04.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To Marylebone. Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.93,0:11:48.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The upper level's full!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.54,0:11:49.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aw!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.00,0:11:53.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be stubborn about it. Come back down.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.44,0:11:54.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.04,0:12:59.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How very naughty! Behave yourself!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.01,0:13:01.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.26,0:13:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma! Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.38,0:13:40.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see it!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.58,0:13:42.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's Kings Cross station, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.35,0:13:44.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.83,0:13:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here now! Don't run!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.01,0:14:12.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Can't you go any faster?!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.01,0:14:15.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That would be dangerous,\Nwe're in the middle of the city.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.45,0:14:17.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care! Go faster!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.55,0:14:19.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.09,0:14:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One third class ticket, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.39,0:14:30.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm afraid third class is full.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.83,0:14:31.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.00,0:14:33.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We still have second class tickets.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.64,0:14:37.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Second... class?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.81,0:14:41.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you'd have come just a bit earlier\Nyou might have gotten into third class.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.34,0:14:44.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's only a difference of 5 or 6 shillings.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.71,0:14:49.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One first class round-trip ticket to York.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.65,0:14:50.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'll it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.19,0:14:54.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that will have to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.42,0:14:55.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Round-trip?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.16,0:14:58.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No... one way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.73,0:15:01.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oranges, oranges!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.83,0:15:04.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're two for a penny!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.77,0:15:07.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Extra! Extra!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:14.24,0:15:17.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the engine of the Midland Railways...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.44,0:15:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and this is the Great Northern. This one here.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.68,0:15:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Really?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.18,0:15:24.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really, really fast.\NIt can hit 50 miles an hour!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.05,0:15:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey now! You're not supposed to doodle there!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.39,0:15:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,'Scuse me! Make way, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.50,0:15:36.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luggage coming through!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.30,0:15:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, it seems we've got the wrong number.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.97,0:15:44.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We still have time to change it,\Nso please hurry back to the ticket window.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.04,0:15:47.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.68,0:15:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm so sorry. I mistook you for someone else.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.81,0:15:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.88,0:15:56.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Madam!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.28,0:16:00.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's really crowded over there too!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.42,0:16:06.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Eh? You mistook her for me?\NWhatever shall I do with you, Madam?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.40,0:16:16.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder if you will notice this letter...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.60,0:16:23.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That we must part this way... it is my one regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.04,0:16:31.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, my heart now feels\Nstrangely peaceful and calm.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.29,0:16:37.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even though our love crossed classes\Nand was never meant to be,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.09,0:16:41.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that our hearts have touched in this way...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.16,0:16:44.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...has meant everything to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.70,0:16:50.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The memories we shared\Nwill stay with me, always.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.77,0:16:57.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter how far away I am,\NI will always pray for your happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.29,0:17:16.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, please buy a flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.60,0:17:17.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How much is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.13,0:17:19.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,One penny.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.80,0:17:21.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll have one, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.81,0:17:28.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.51,0:17:32.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May the grace of God go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.75,0:17:42.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oranges, oranges! Sweet, delicious oranges!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:49.90,0:17:52.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The train is about to depart.\NPlease hurry to your seats!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.85,0:18:11.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.21,0:18:32.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Jones...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.68,0:18:38.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.32,0:18:51.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma, l...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.13,0:18:52.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.59,0:18:53.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.43,0:19:01.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.27,0:19:05.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.94,0:19:45.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.49,0:19:52.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.03,0:20:06.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Emma!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:55.95,0:20:57.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sir?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.29,0:21:02.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please buy a flower.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.17,0:21:14.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.57,0:21:17.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,May the grace of God go with you.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.18,0:21:26.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's beautiful...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.48,0:21:29.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's a lily of the valley, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.65,0:21:34.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes... though I'm not sure why I bought it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.42,0:21:38.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, don't worry about that!\NFlowers are great to have anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.06,0:21:43.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In the "language of flowers," that lily is\Nwonderful, too. Do you know what it means?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.50,0:21:44.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:45.43,0:21:49.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It means that "happiness will return."
